result.name: The Great Restaurant

reviews.text:
A dry hotpot with chicken base soup. It tastes very unique, mara spicy and smoky flavour. First a basic ceramic pot comes with chicken. It is kind of dry and adjustable for spicy level. After enjoying chicken, you may add chicken soup and enjoy hotpot for more choices of yours,

It tastes sweet, spicy, smoky and thick chicken, so you can't stop your chopsticks untill the end. Be careful not to make the bottom of the pot burn. Stir it often. 

It is always busy here. You can also take it out to home.
Very delicious chicken pot for an excellent price! The sauce is delicious after its finished cooking with the chicken and we usually spoon it over white rice.

The first time I came here, I ate raw chicken. We didn't realise that the chicken hot pot required a bit of cooking first before it was ready. Give it 10 to 15 mins to cook before eating. You won't need to pour any broth at this stage. Just keep the pot covered and stir it occasionally. If you need help, seek the assistance of the waiters. They will make sure you don't eat raw chicken. Once you are done eating the chicken, add in the broth to cook the rest of the items. The hot pot here is of good value. It taste good and portions are large enough. Expect to spend about HKD150 per person.
A nice Japanese restaurant specializing at pork chops, etc!!!
Strong and deep taste.

reviews.text: 한국에서 유행중인 마라 맛집이라고 입소문을 타도 좋을듯한 집이다. 5:30 오픈전에 줄서있다가 들어갔는데 카운터에 앉아있는 숏컷 아주머니외에 영어 소통불가. (다행히 옆테이블 현지인 친구에게 도움요청) 영어메뉴 없음. 기본적으로 마라닭볶음탕을 먹은 후 육수를 부어 샤브샤브로 먹는다. 맛은 딱 매콤 마라 닭볶음탕 ㅋㅋ 샤브메뉴는 옆테이블 눈치코치 잘보고 시키면 될듯하고. 식사시간이 90분 한정이니 주의할것. 강추는 생선껍질 튀김인데 현지인들이 많이 먹어 시켰음. 먹어보면 왜 많이 먹는지 알게됨 ㅋㅋ 샤브 안하고 그냥 먹어도 맛있음. 그리고 나올때 보니 대기줄로 가득 차있었다.

It tastes sweet, spicy, smoky and thick chicken, so you can't stop your chopsticks untill the end. Be careful not to make the bottom of the pot burn. Stir it often. 

It is always busy here. You can also take it out to home.
好吃好好味 但好貴
並不是好味，沒有正宗的四川麻辣。
Very delicious chicken pot for an excellent price! The sauce is delicious after its finished cooking with the chicken and we usually spoon it over white rice.
